# Protocol RE TODO

This TODO reflects the current codebase and README. The project already has a
working staged pipeline, feature extraction, relation inference, semantic
labeling, and Markdown export. The highest-priority work is to make the default
PCAP workflow match the README and to improve evidence quality.

## 1. Make one command build `data/01_messages.jsonl` from a PCAP folder

Status: Implemented; needs broader end-to-end validation on real PCAP sets.

- Done: `main.py` now defaults to the PCAP workflow and uses the provided input
  folder instead of always reading `archive/protocol-x-payloads`.
- Done: the runner merges stages 1 to 3:
  - collect PCAP/PCAPNG files from the input folder into `pcaps/`
  - deduplicate collected captures
  - extract canonical messages into `data/01_messages.jsonl`
- Done: `scripts/03_alt_build_corpus.py` remains available through
  `--legacy-json <dir>` for archived extracted JSON payloads.
- Done: added runner flags for `--legacy-json`, `--skip-collect`,
  `--service-port`, `--max-workers`, `--data-dir`, `--pcap-dir`,
  `--output-dir`, `--family-sample-size`, and `--stop-after`.
- Done: the runner creates output directories before steps write files.
- Done: README examples now document the default PCAP workflow and legacy JSON
  compatibility mode.
- Remaining: run the full PCAP path on representative captures and decide
  whether deduplication should always delete duplicates or become configurable.

## 2. Improve PCAP message reconstruction

Status: Partially implemented; needs broader validation.

- Done: `src/protocol_re/io/extract_payloads.py` supports optional
  `reassembly_mode="stream"` in addition to the default packet-payload mode.
- Done: packet-level extraction remains the default fast fallback.
- Done: stream mode sorts directional TCP segments by sequence number, trims
  retransmission overlap, ignores duplicate covered bytes, and splits chunks at
  sequence gaps.
- Done: stream-extracted records include metadata such as `extraction_mode`,
  `framing`, stream offsets, TCP sequence range, and gap indicators.
- Done: stream mode is protocol-agnostic; it emits raw reconstructed TCP byte
  streams and does not assume any known grammar.
- Done: `--service-port` is optional; without it, PCAP extraction treats all TCP
  payloads as candidate unknown-protocol traffic instead of assuming a specific
  industrial protocol port.
- Done: `scripts/03_extract_messages.py` and `main.py` expose
  `--reassembly-mode packet|stream`.
- Done: README documents packet vs stream extraction modes for unknown
  protocols.
- Remaining: validate against larger real PCAP sets with out-of-order traffic,
  retransmissions, and unknown industrial protocols.
- Remaining: add committed tests/fixtures for split TCP application payloads.

## 3. Use extracted feature artifacts throughout the model

Status: Complete for the current pipeline baseline.

- `scripts/05_extract_features.py` and `src/protocol_re/features/extraction.py`
  already generate per-message and per-family features.
- Done: `main.py` wires `data/03_features/family_features.json` into
  `scripts/06_infer_boundaries.py` and `scripts/12_build_protocol_model.py`
  using `--features-json`.
- Done: README step-by-step commands include `--features-json` so boundary
  inference and protocol model output include feature summaries.
- Done: family feature artifacts now include `motif_stats.ngram_frequencies`
  with top aggregate n-gram counts and frequencies per width.
- Done: README documents the n-gram frequency tables.
- Done: boundary inference uses family entropy, uniqueness, and coverage vectors
  to adjust segment confidence and attach feature evidence.
- Future enhancement: use feature vectors directly in family clustering, beyond
  the current clustering byte-vector path.

## 4. Add deeper repetition and structure detection

Status: Complete for feature-artifact baseline; deeper parser inference can build on it.

- Done: current feature extraction detects run-lengths and repeated 2/3-byte
  n-grams.
- Done: family feature artifacts include wider repeated motifs for 4/5/6/8-byte
  subsequences under `motif_stats.wide_repeated_motifs`.
- Done: family feature artifacts include trailing data block and padding hints
  under `structure_stats.trailing_block_stats`.
- Done: family feature artifacts include fixed, mostly fixed, or variable length
  profiles under `structure_stats.length_profile`.
- Done: family feature artifacts include recurring fixed-position byte groups
  under `structure_stats.recurring_field_groups`.
- Done: these structure features are carried into `protocol_model.json` through
  family feature summaries and are available to the next LLM evidence exporter.
- Future enhancement: use these structure hints directly in boundary splitting
  and semantic labeling, not only as exported evidence.

## 5. Add an LLM evidence exporter

Status: Implemented.

- Done: added `src/protocol_re/export/llm_evidence.py` and
  `scripts/14_export_llm_evidence.py`.
- Done: exports a compact per-family evidence bundle for downstream LLM
  analysis to `output/llm_evidence.json` from `main.py`.
- Done: includes templates, segment stats, top examples, length histograms,
  entropy/uniqueness/coverage vector digests, repeated motifs, structure hints,
  request/response links, echo fields, length relations, semantic candidates,
  and confidence notes.
- Done: kept separate from generic `protocol_model.json` and trims vectors,
  relations, motifs, and labels for token efficiency.
- Future enhancement: add Markdown or prompt-template rendering for specific LLM
  workflows.

## 6. Add evaluation and reporting

Status: Implemented for JSON metrics; tests remain future work.

- Done: added `src/protocol_re/evaluation/reporting.py` and
  `scripts/15_evaluate_pipeline.py`.
- Done: writes `data/11_evaluation.json` from `main.py`.
- Done: reports corpus message/session/source counts and payload-length
  distributions.
- Done: reports family assignment coverage, unassigned/noise counts, cluster
  size distribution, assignment sample size, and clustering feature shape.
- Done: reports boundary parseability, segment/field count distributions,
  confidence summaries, template lengths, and feature-evidence coverage.
- Done: reports pair counts, score distributions, latency distributions,
  direction-known vs direction-unknown ratios, and pairing modes.
- Done: reports relation edge counts, pair-count/score distributions, echo
  support, length-relation support, role-hint counts, and top family edges.
- Future enhancement: add committed regression tests for representative pipeline
  stages.

